    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2 id="Yintong-Shang"><a href="#Yintong-Shang" class="headerlink" title="Yintong Shang"></a>Yintong Shang</h2><p>A senior undergraduate student fascinated by and dedicated to computer graphics.  I aspire to be a technical artist, who grasps knowledge and skills in both art and programming.  </p><h3 id="Interests"><a href="#Interests" class="headerlink" title="Interests"></a>Interests</h3><p>computer graphics, simulation and physics-based animation, shape reconstrution, physics-based rendering  </p><h3 id="Experiences"><a href="#Experiences" class="headerlink" title="Experiences"></a>Experiences</h3><p>Research Project: Precise Calibration and Modeling of Piezo-resistive Textile      2020.3-2021.9  </p><p>Advisor: <a href="http://pplab.ustc.edu.cn/main.htm">Prof. Jingyuan Cheng</a>, <a href="http://en.cs.ustc.edu.cn/">School of Computer Science and Technology</a>, <a href="http://en.ustc.edu.cn/">USTC</a>  </p><p>◦ Realized a mathematical model to predict the nonlinear behavior of piezoresistive textile  </p><p>◦ Built a finite-element physical model of the textile  </p><h3 id="Education"><a href="#Education" class="headerlink" title="Education"></a>Education</h3><p>Bachelor of Engineering in Electronic Science and Technology at <a href="http://en.ustc.edu.cn/">University of Science and Technology of China</a>, 2018-2022  </p><h3 id="Skills"><a href="#Skills" class="headerlink" title="Skills"></a>Skills</h3><p>◦ Python (4000 lines, including Taichi)  </p><p>◦ C++ (3000 lines, including OpenGL)  </p><p>◦ C# (1200 lines, for Unity)  </p><p>◦ MATLAB (500 lines)  </p><p>◦ COMSOL (finite-element simulation, on Structural Mechanics and Electromagnetics)  </p><p>◦ Cinema 4D (created animations for fun)  </p><h3 id="Useful-Links"><a href="#Useful-Links" class="headerlink" title="Useful Links"></a>Useful Links</h3><p><a href="http://games-cn.org/">GAMES (Graphics And Mixed Environment Seminar)</a>  </p><p><a href="http://kesen.realtimerendering.com/">Siggraph paper collection</a>  </p><figure class="highlight markdown"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="section"># a markdown test</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="section">#include <span class="xml">&lt;glad/glad.h&gt;</span></span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="section">#include <span class="xml">&lt;GLFW/glfw3.h&gt;</span></span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="section">#include <span class="xml">&lt;stb/stb_image.h&gt;</span></span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="section">#include <span class="xml">&lt;glm/glm.hpp&gt;</span></span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="section">#include <span class="xml">&lt;glm/gtc/matrix_transform.hpp&gt;</span></span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="section">#include <span class="xml">&lt;glm/gtc/type_ptr.hpp&gt;</span></span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="Contact"><a href="#Contact" class="headerlink" title="Contact"></a>Contact</h3><p>e-mail: <a href="mailto:&#x73;&#104;&#x61;&#121;&#105;&#116;&#111;&#95;&#x40;&#111;&#x75;&#116;&#108;&#x6f;&#111;&#x6b;&#x2e;&#99;&#x6f;&#x6d;">&#x73;&#104;&#x61;&#121;&#105;&#116;&#111;&#95;&#x40;&#111;&#x75;&#116;&#108;&#x6f;&#111;&#x6b;&#x2e;&#99;&#x6f;&#x6d;</a>  </p>]]></content>
    
    
      
      
